<!---pseudo class = its a keyword added to selector that specifies a special state of the selected element-->

CSS:

a:link{
    color:green;
}
a:visited{
    color:blue;
}
a:hover{
    color:aquamarine;
}
a:active{
    color:yellow
}
button:hover{
    background-color: lightcoral;
}
li:nth-child(even) {
    background-color: yellow;
}
li:nth-child(odd) {
    background-color: grey;
}
/*
a:link: The default style for a link you haven't clicked yet.

a:visited: The style for a link you have already visited.

a:hover: The style when you move your mouse over the link.

a:active: The style for the exact moment you click the link.
*/
